International Brief -- British Telecommunications PLC:
   Firm to Trim Work Force
   By 10%-12% in Fiscal '93
In a letter to employees, BT Chairman I.D. Vallance said
the company would use "every practicable means to achieve
this on a voluntary basis." He said details of a new
voluntary release program would circulate in early April. The
plan "will provide leavers with generous financial
compensation together with practical help to further their
careers outside BT," the chairman said.